# Vellum Assistant — Web App Environment Variables
#
# Copy to `.env.local` to override defaults during local development.
# Vite loads `.env.local` automatically and it is gitignored.
#
# All client-side env vars MUST use the VITE_ prefix — Vite only exposes
# prefixed variables to browser code via `import.meta.env`.
# Reference: https://vite.dev/guide/env-and-mode.html

# ── Auth ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When "true", the React Router auth middleware redirects unauthenticated
# users to /account/login. When unset or any other value, auth is
# optional — users can use the app without logging in.
#
# Hosted deployments (vellum.ai, App Store iOS) set this to "true" in CI.
# Local dev and self-hosted/open-source builds leave it unset (default).
#
# To test auth-required mode locally:
#   VITE_AUTH_REQUIRED=true bun run dev
#
# VITE_AUTH_REQUIRED=true
